		(uuid "0ac3b9bc-f1cf-430f-854b-d3eb6f68aece")
	)
	(text_box "STM32 Pin Functions / Software Blueprint\n\nSelf VBUS Muxer Status\n- PB4(pin-28): ST_HUB_VBUS		: GPI	- ext. PU	- H = HOST-A / L = HOST-B\n\nDownstream VBUS Muxer Control & Status\n- PC14(pin-2): FLT_HOSTB_VBUS#	: GPI	- ext. PU	- H = no fault / L = fault Host-B\n- PC15(pin-3): FLT_HOSTA_VBUS#	: GPI	- ext. PU	- H = no fault / L = fault Host-A\n- PB5(pin-29): EN_VBUSB 		: GPO 	- ext. PD	- H = enable VBUS of Host-B / L = disable VBUS of Host-B\n- PB8(pin-32): EN_VBUSA 		: GPO	- ext. PD	- H = enable VBUS of Host-A / L = disable VBUS of Host-A\n\nUSB Data Muxer Control\n- PB2(pin-17): HOSTMUX_OE#		: GPO	- ext. PU	- H = Disable Downstream USB Host\n- PB3(pin-27): HOSTMUX_SEL		: GPO	- ext. PU	- H = Select HOST-A / L = Select HOST-B\n\nHub Control\n- PA15(pin-26): RESET#			: GPO	- ext. PD	- H = disable Hub RESET# / L = Enable Hub RESET#, see Note *2)\n- PA8(pin-18): PGANG			: GPI	- ext. PU	- H = Hub normal operation / L = Hub suscpend mode\n- PB6(pin-30): I2C_SCL_HUB		: I2C1_SCL = AF6	- SMBUS Hub Control\n- PB7(pin-31): I2C_SDA_HUB		: I2C1_SDA = AF6	- SMBUS Hub Control\n- PA11(pin-22): MCU_D-			: USB_DM = Additional Function	- Hub Port #4\n- PA12(pin-23): MCU_D+			: USB_DP = Additional Function	- Hub Port #4\n\nVoltage Measurement\n- PA0(pin-7): HOSTA_VBUS_MEAS	: ADC_IN0 = Additional Function\n- PA1(pin-8): HOSTB_VBUS_MEAS	: ADC_IN1 = Additional Function\n- PA7(pin-14): DS_VBUS_MEAS		: ADC_IN7 = Additional Function\n\nCurrent Measurement\n- PA4(pin-11): DS1_CURSENSE		: ADC_IN4 = Additional Function\n- PA5(pin-12): DS2_CURSENSE		: ADC_IN5 = Additional Function\n- PA6(pin-13): DS3_CURSENSE		: ADC_IN6 = Additional Function\n\nUser Interface\n- PC6(pin-20): LEDR# 			: GPO or TIM3_CH1 = AF1 or TIM2_CH3 = AF2 as PWM\n- PB0(pin-15): LEDB# 			: GPO or TIM3_CH3 = AF1 as PWM\n- PB1(pin-16): LEDG# 			: GPO or TIM3_CH4 = AF1 or TIM14_CH1 = AF0 as PWM\n- PB9(pin-1): SWITCH			: GPI	- ext. PD	- H = Switch active / L = Switch inactive, see Note *1)\n- PA9(pin-19): I2C_SCL_UI		: I2C2_SCL = AF8	- external display control\n- PA10(pin-21): I2C_SDA_UI		: I2C2_SDA = AF8	- external display control\n\nDebug Interface\n- PF2-NRST(pin-6): NRST#		: NRST = Additional Function\n- PA2(pin-9): DBG_UART_TX		: USART2_TX = AF1 (Bootloader-Support)\n- PA3(pin-10): DBG_UART_RX		: USART2_RX	= AF1 (Bootloader-Support)\n- PA13(pin-24): DBG_SWDIO		: SWDIO = AF0\n- PA14-BOOT0(pin-25): DBG_SWCLK	: SWCLK = AF0\n\nNotes\n*1) When PA15 is driven Low, Switch activation will not be detectable, because SWITCH will be Low, too!\n*2) When Switch is activated during power-up (@ PA15, PB2 = HiZ): 1. RESET# is driven H, 2. HOSTMUX_OE# is driven L\n\n\n\n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 261.62 13.97 0)
		(size 144.78 119.38)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
