		(uuid "1f0a7f91-f38b-45c3-85c9-0258477877ad")
	)
	(text_box "Feature List\n- PCB 63 x 20 mm USB stick form factor.\n- One out of two USB 2.0 host interfaces is user selectable as upstream host for three downstream ports.\n- Downstream ports are host powered per host selection, max. 1.5 Amps host current with automatic current limiter.\n- Measurment of Host A, Host B and downstream voltage plus each of three downstream load currents.\n- User interface with a tactile switch button, a RGB status LED and an optional 64 x 32 Pixel OLED display.\n\nUse Cases\n- Hub for Keyboard / Mouse peripherals and muxing between two host PCs (\"Home Office\")\n- USB hub with voltage & current monitoring\n- voltage & current monitoring for charging applications\n- USB to UART and/or I2C bridge\n- ...\n\nList of technical features\n- 2x USB 2.0 Type A Plug for Twin Host connection\n- 3x USB 2.0 Type A Receptables for Triple Peripherals\n- 1x GL852G 4-Port USB 2.0 Hub\n- 1x STM32 on fourth Downstream Port\n- Automatic selection of Host powering the local devices (GL852, STM32)\n- STM32 for system control with following functions\n  - selection of USB Host VBUS sourcing Downstream Power\n  - selection / muxing of USB Host as Upstream Host\n  - measurement of Host A / Host B VBUS voltage\n  - measurement of Downstream VBUS voltage\n  - maeasurement of each Downstream supply current\n  - Hub management via SMBus (I2C)\n  - management of the user interface\n- User Interface\n  - RGB-LED\n  - Tactile Switch Button\n  - I2C interface for display control\n- STM32 Debug interface"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 31.75 20.32 0)
		(size 97.79 81.28)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
